<br>
The facts of DAoC speak for themselves.<br>
<br>
1. The game is not finished. It is poorly balanced, devoid of content, and its developers have zero idea what they are doing.<br>
<br>
2. It is a game where the only thing to do at high levels is to kill other players. For PvP to work, someone has to be a victim. Most people don't care to play victims.<br>
<br>
3. It's leveling treadmill is much much worse than EQ's, due to having far less to do. And you can't participate in the RvR as anything but a target dummy until at least L30.<br>
<br>
People have been deserting DAoC for months. Its high player mark does not get much over 30k anymore (was routinely over 40k in October) and continues to drop.<br>
<br>
And there is much MUCH less roleplaying, on roleplay servers or off. You're outright lying if you say otherwise.<br>
<br>
A clue for you, free of charge. There is a reason 99% of EQ players didn't switch. DAoC isn't a very good game. It is EQ with most the fun parts missing.<br>
<br>
Feel free to continue to beg for players, though. Some of us will always be around to set the record straight.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unimiane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimiane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 12:39:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> I played DAoC for a couple of months and then came back to EQ - I found I cared very little for PvP and that I prefered EQ's combat system.  I have friends who stayed in DAoC, prefering it over EQ.  To each their own.<br>
<br>
But what I think was the most significant nail in the coffin for me was the low amount of roleplaying on the &quot;Roleplaying Enforced&quot; servers - particularly in the Hibernia and Albion realms (Midgard seemed a little better overall in terms of people looking to RP).   If you think FV is bad in terms of Roleplay, try being on a server where there are specific rules that prohibit you from having a name or speaking in public channels in a manner that is not representative of the time and realm setting, and watch as only a small subset of the server seems to be able to follow the rules, or even understand them.  <br>
<br>
There were .. shall we say .. lively debates around people's interpretation of very specific rules, such as &quot;No, when they say &quot;absolutely no public speech outside the time/realm&quot; they really mean no d00d speech, so if I want to say &quot;AFK, taking a leak&quot; while grouped, that is my perogative, stop being a RP nazi and help make this server fun for everyone&quot;.  Another lively debate was around the fact that a vast majority of the players were ex-EQ and wanted to talk and play as if they were still in EQ (inc, AFK, tank/mezzer/etc), causing a great amount of consternation for the &quot;I hate Verant&quot; RP crowd.  <br>
<br>
Making matters worse, rather than have the rules enforced by CS to help clear up the debate, players were expected to police the server because CS was too overloaded to have anything but 10 day response times and only then to major occurances and not RP infractions.  And, really, there isn't much you can do as a player about people named things like &quot;Danish Skilz&quot; &quot;Juici Fruiti&quot; and &quot;Jeddi Master&quot;, or truly offensive names (&quot;Stickysaks&quot; shouting in Jordheim about his friend &quot;Limpdick&quot; comes to mind) or any number of the people talking completely out of character on a constant basis.  I was concerned that the longer this went on, the harder it would be to change, and after multiple e-mails asking when they would start enforcing the RP rules, if ever, went unanswered I finally left the game in frustration.  I understand from my friends still there that RP is not enforced.<br>
<br>
As far as I'm concerned, I'm happier where they set my expectations that RP is &quot;encouraged&quot; rather than think I'm going somewhere it is enforced, only to find out that it isn't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utherrinaldaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TherrinAldaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 2:12:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Funny, I don't think EQ is so desperate for people that they send their drooling fanboys to troll DAoC server forums for players....<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
