For what it is worth, I wanted to add that I hoped my post wasn't taken as undermining the roleplayers that are there in DAoC, and I did encounter many.  Many of us talk about how &quot;nobody&quot; roleplays both here on FV and in DAoC, which isn't quite fair to those who continue to do so.  <br>
<br>
I think that FV and DAoC roleplay is very similar - some guilds and individuals do an excellent job of roleplaying, others do not. However,  I expected that from FV, not from DAoC where I expected roleplay would be enforced, so Dark Age was more disappointing.  Which isn't to say that it would for everyone, particularly if you go in knowing that RP is not enforced. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umollycat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mollycat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 4:08:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;And good riddance to me, i wont be responding anymore.<br>
